Listening to Skratch Bastid's Satisfaction Guaranteed mix. 78 min of funky freash beats, cant be beat.
Working those Supply and Demand equations... Kelly, you better be nice to me this time around, considering the time Im putting in.
Fight broke out after the coin toss. Wild.
Anthem by former creed frontman. You can tell.
Headed to the champs bowl. Go Bagers!
Having a great time in Florida, beaches are nice and sunny. Looking to finally beat the farmer's tan back for a few weeks.
Feet in the ocean, strange christmas indeed.
Finally pulled in, got on the net for this last post. Im out for the night.
Just got done with another driving stint, my milage this trip is impressive. Lets finish this trip. 3 hours.
Dilapitated housing is a theme round these parts. Greg drools on his pillow when he sleeps. Refuses to actually rest his head, giraffe-like.
Number of trashed school buses Ive seen along the road: high twenties. Palm trees. low teens. Georgia has strange sights to be seen.
Just finishing up the watchmen. About 8 hours away now!
All these towns seem to be made up of the same few building blocks. Wendys. Waffle house. Mcdonalds. Repeat.
Wasnt fully prepared for the accents... A guitar strums in my mind whenever our waitress talks. Or drawls. Or whatever she does with her ...
Sitting in a waffle house in the southern part of tenn. Across the street, a mcdonalds sells fifty nuggets for ten bucks. Amazing, i know.
Just got done driving for a few hours. Yeah no biggie. In tennesse. I guess were really serious about this whole goin to florida thing.
Reststop has an exclusivity music deal with aerosmith, methinks. Andrea still has a deal with the crabby and mean whiney noises.
Gregs ear has been taunting me for the last couple hours. To Wet willie or not to wet willie? That is the ? I think we all know the answer
Sister looks like voldemort with her hood up. Note to self: search her bag for horcruxes when we stop.
Just had my first genuine want for plane tickets for this trip. With it, comes self-reflection, and a greater knowledge of my limits. Lolz.
Man this book is long. Neck hurts, and we are moving at a slushy crawl on the interstate. Maybe ill drive soon? Kinda want to crank radio.
Smells like a bears win here in this illinois truck stop. Greg tells me vault drinks like a soda and kicks like an energy drink.
